 protein, which are important morphogens for a wide range of developmental
 processes, including anteroposterior patterns of limbs and regulation of
 left-right asymmetry in embryonic development. Multiple cell-surface
 receptors are responsible for transducing and/or regulating HH signals. The
 HHIP encoded by this gene is a highly conserved, vertebrate-specific
 inhibitor of HH signaling. It interacts with all three HH family members,
